Section 1:
1 L.D. 552
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 INLAND FISHERIES AND WILDLIFE
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 204, L.D. 552, “An Act to Create an
10 Outfitter License for Owners and Operators of Hunting, Fishing and Recreation Businesses
11 Who Are Not Maine Guides”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Amend the Laws Governing the Carrying Passengers for Hire License'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
15 following:
16 'Sec. 1. 12 MRSA §12853, sub-§7, ¶E is enacted to read:
17 E. A person who is certified in first aid under subsection 4, paragraph C and has
18 satisfactorily completed a towed water sports safety education course under section
19 13063 may, without a guide license, operate a watercraft in the course of employment
20 with a seasonal business engaged in instruction in recreational activities.
21 Sec. 2. 12 MRSA §13063, sub-§1, as amended by PL 2019, c. 324, §3, is further
22 amended to read:
23 1. Prohibition. A person may not operate a motorboat carrying passengers for hire
24 without having successfully completed a boater safety education course approved by a
25 national association of state boating law administrators and approved by the commissioner
26 or a towed water sports safety education course administered by the department and
27 approved by the commissioner. A person operating a motorboat carrying passengers for
28 hire shall provide proof of having successfully completed a course under this subsection
29 when requested by the commissioner or the commissioner's agent. For purposes of this
30 section, "carrying passengers for hire" means receiving remuneration to carry passengers
31 in a motorboat from one predetermined point to another predetermined point on inland
32 waters.
33 A. A person who violates this subsection commits a civil violation for which a fine of
34 not less than $100 nor more than $500 may be adjudged.
Page 1 - 132LR2318(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 204, L.D. 552
1 B. A person who violates this subsection after having been adjudicated as having
2 committed 3 or more civil violations under this Part within the previous 5-year period
3 commits a Class E crime.
4 Sec. 3. 12 MRSA §13063, sub-§2, as amended by PL 2019, c. 324, §3, is further
5 amended to read:
6 2. Requirement. Every operator of a motorboat, other than a licensed Maine guide
7 certified in watercraft safety, carrying passengers for hire, except those operators who have
8 been issued and have or are required to have in their possession a current valid federal
9 operator's license, shall show proof of having successfully completed an approved boater
10 safety education course or a towed water sports safety education course in accordance with
11 subsection 1 upon request of the commissioner or the commissioner's agent.'
12 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
13 number to read consecutively.
14 SUMMARY
1155 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. The amendment allows a person
1166 who has completed a towed water sports safety education course and is certified in first aid
1177 to operate a watercraft without a guide license as an employee of a seasonal business
1188 engaged in instruction in recreational activities.
1199 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
2200 (See attached)
Page 2 - 132LR2318(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
